==English==

===Etymology===
English ''athel, adel or aethel'', noble (Webster's 1828).
From Old English ''aethelu'' nobility.

===Adjective===
#[[noble]]

==Tatar==

===Etymology===
English [[athel#English|athel]], noble, Old English ''aethelu'', nobility.
Common Germanic: Swedish ''ädel'', Deutsch ''adel''. Also Scots Gaelic ''uasal''.

  
===Adjective===

#[[athel#English|athel]], [[noble]]. The word ''athel'' (or ''adel''), is in many Tatar proper names, as '''Athel'''herei, noble hero; '''Athelbek''', noble ruler;
